sec.p:
Rotational equilibrium of the forces is satisfied by taking the moments about the neutral-axis
(7)Mu=Cc*0.85c>/2+Cs*>(c-d')+N*(w/2-c)+Ts1*>(h1-c>)+Ts2*>(h2-c>)+Ts3*>(h3-c>)
where


Cc: the compressive force of the concrete; w : the section width of the column;

c: the distance from the compression face of the section to the neutral axis;

fc’: the unconfined compressive strength of the concrete;

Cs: the compressive force of the steel; εsc : the compressive strain of the steel;

Asc: the section area of compressive steel; Es : the elastic modulus of steel;

fy: the yielding stress of steel; Tsi(i = 1,2,3) : the tension force of steel at site i; εi(i = 1,2,3) : the strain of steel at site i; Asi(i = 1,2,3) is the section area of steel at site i;

N: the axial load on the column; Mu : the ultimate bending moment of a columnar section; d’ : the distance from the section face to the site of compressive steel;

h: the length of the column section; hi(i = 1,2,3) : the distance from the section face to the site of tensile steel i.

(i) For εc≦0.002 k
(8)fc=kfc'[2ɛc/0.002k-(ɛc/0.002k)2]
(9)k=1+ρsfyh/fc'
(ii) For εc>0.002 k:
(10)fc=kfc'[1-Zm(ɛc/0.002k)2]≥0.2kfc'
(11)Zm=0.53+0.26fc'145fc'-1000+34ρsh″sh-0.002K(mpa)
Where


εc: the strain of the confined concrete; fc : the stress of the confined concrete;

fc’: the compressive strength of the concrete which is unconfined;

fyh: the yield stress of the confining steel;

ρs: the lateral volumetric ratio of the steel measured outside the hoops;

h”: the width of the confined core measured outside the hoops;

sh: the center to center spacing of the hoop sets.
